article.headline: Stony Brook 63, Colgate 54
article.story: STONY BROOK, N.Y. -- Bryan Dougher scored 15 points to lead Stony Brook to a 63-54 victory over Colgate on Wednesday night. Anthony Mayo added 10 points for the Seawolves (5-6), who won despite shooting 52.2 percent from the free-throw line (12 of 23) and being outrebounded 40-34. Colgate (0-11) entered as one of the 14 winless Division I teams in the country and is off to its worst start since going 0-13 to start the 1986-87 season. The Raiders led 33-32, but the Seawolves took the lead for good on Dallis Joyner's jumper with 15:21 to play. That started a 9-0 run that gave Stony Brook a 41-33 lead on Anthony Mayo's three-point play with 13:20 remaining. Colgate cut the lead to 51-49 with 5:06 to play, but Stony Brook pushed it to 57-50 with 57 seconds left. Mayo added 10 points for the Seawolves. Yaw Gyawu and Pat Moore scored 13 points each for Colgate.
